    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with a clear emphasis on exploiting favorable pitching matchups to offset the scarcity of our stolen base targets. The undisputed cornerstone of today\u2019s lineup is **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (80.98), who benefits from a prime matchup against Sasaki (5.52 xERA). His elite sprint speed is a massive asset in our 5x5 build, and with wind conditions favoring hitters, he is poised for a high-ceiling performance despite hitting eighth. Joining him as a priority start is **Junior Caminero** (71.50) and **Trea Turner** (70.16). **Trea Turner** remains our premier catalyst at the top of the order; while facing Elder (4.29 xERA) is a standard test, his projected production is anchored by his ability to generate counting stats in both runs and steals.\n\nWe are navigating a few strategic bottlenecks today, most notably the benching of **Victor Scott II** (38.48). Despite his elite speed profile, his matchup against a difficult Woo (3.30 xERA) and an unfavorable slot at the bottom of the order suppressed his efficiency below our 40.0 floor. We are forced to prioritize the higher raw output of **Colt Keith** (61.81) and **Kyle Schwarber** (66.62), the latter of whom carries an elite xwOBA of .402 into his matchup against Elder. While **Caleb Durbin** (55.61) provides a nice park-factor boost, we are keeping a close eye on **Dillon Dingler** (44.06) and **Chase Meidroth** (50.85); both are marginal starts, but they are playing to avoid burning unnecessary game caps while still offering exposure to favorable park conditions.\n\nRisk management remains our primary concern regarding the health and availability of our bench. With **Christian Yelich** firmly on the IL and **Carson Benge** suffering a total game postponement, our flexibility is limited. We are monitoring **Hyeseong Kim** (57.38) closely, as his upside is capped by his spot in the batting order, yet his platoon advantage against Rea makes him a safer play than the remaining options on the bench. We remain positioned to capitalize on these specific pitching vulnerabilities, hoping that our emphasis on speed-focused starters like **Pete Crow-Armstrong** will bridge the gap in a tight league race.",
